OL,6,FMr Thomas told the Court of Appeal in
OL,7,FLondon that it had been a "joint
OL,8,Fendeavour" to travel to the UK, and
OL,9,Fthat Bah's actions "meant that a
OL,10,Fpassage to the UK was available, so
OL,11,Ftragically the deceased availed
OL,12,Fthemselves of that passage".
OL,14,FThe Crown Prosecution Service (CPS)
OL,15,Fopposed the appeal bid.
OL,17,FDuncan Atkinson KC, for the CPS,
OL,18,Fpreviously said: "This is a case where
OL,19,Fthe passengers on the boat were acting
OL,20,Fin concert with their pilot."
